Ivanhoé Cambridge develops and invests in high-quality real estate properties, projects and companies that are shaping the urban fabric in dynamic cities around the world. It does so responsibly, with a view to generate long-term performance. Ivanhoé Cambridge is committed to creating living spaces that foster the well-being of people and communities, while reducing its environmental footprint.

Ivanhoé Cambridge invests internationally alongside strategic partners and major real estate funds that are leaders in their markets. Through subsidiaries and partnerships, the Company holds interests in more than 1,000 buildings, primarily in the industrial and logistics, office, residential and retail sectors. Ivanhoé Cambridge held close to C$60,4 billion in real estate assets as at December 31, 2020 and is a real estate subsidiary of the Caisse de dépôt et placement du Québec (cdpq.com), one of Canada's leading institutional fund managers. For more information: ivanhoecambridge.com.


Department : Office, North America

Position type : Salaried
SPECIFIC ACCOUNTABILITIES

The Investment, Offices, North America team is responsible for all investment activities related to acquisitions, dispositions and financing. Its mandate is to identify investment opportunities that will generate stable long-term returns for the Company. The team’s aim is to optimize its portfolio in order to be active in the various major markets in North America.


As the Senior Analyst, Investment, Offices, North America, you will help team members with the acquisition, disposition and financing of real estate assets. You will also be called upon to assist your asset management colleagues as needed with certain tasks related to the North American office portfolio.

Your main duties will include the following:
Assist the Senior Vice President, Investments, in analyzing real estate deals;
Prepare investment project analyses, including detailed financial analyses, during investment transactions;
Complete the initial underwriting for investment projects, vet opportunities and make recommendations;
Review the various documents during the course of the transaction and adjust preliminary analyses as required;
Serve as a resource person and coordinate transaction operations with other internal and external stakeholders;
Contribute actively to the due diligence process, the preparation of presentations and the drafting of investment proposal reports for various internal committees;
Monitor target markets and maintain a network of industry contacts (appraisers, brokers, managers, etc.) to ensure access to the latest information in order to accurately assess markets and investment projects;
Participate in negotiating deals entrusted to the supervisor;
Active participation in coordinating interactions with the portfolio management, development, finance, taxation, legal affairs and risk management teams;
Perform any other related tasks as assigned by the immediate supervisor or required as part of the job.


KEY REQUIREMENTS
Bachelor’s degree in finance, administration, real estate or accounting. Master’s degree an asset;
C.App., CPA, CFA or the equivalent an asset;
Three to five years of relevant experience;
Proven financial modelling skills;
Keen interest in the real estate investment field;
High-level proficiency in Word, Excel and PowerPoint. Familiarity with Argus, an asset;
Available to work flexible hours;
Ability to work under pressure and with tight deadlines;
Ability to establish solid ties with internal and external stakeholders;
Solid integrative and information presentation skills; outgoing, dynamic and detail-oriented;
Excellent command of written and spoken French and English; good writing skills.


If you are interested in this challenge, please submit your resume.


YOU HAVE EVERYTHING TO GAIN!

When you join the Ivanhoé Cambridge team, you are eligible for employment benefits and a pension plan that are among the best in the industry. Our many health and wellness programs encourage you to balance your work and personal lives and fulfil your desire for social involvement, while maintaining a healthy lifestyle. At Ivanhoé Cambridge, you will have many opportunities to develop your skills and thrive professionally, in Canada or elsewhere in the world. Our initiatives aimed at creating an exceptional working environment that inspires our employees to give the best of themselves elevated Ivanhoé Cambridge into the ranks of 100 Top Employers in Canada.

Ivanhoé Cambridge’s commitment to diversity and inclusion spans the breadth of its operations. Accommodations are available upon request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the selection process. We take pride in creating a working environment where everyone is set up for success. Please advise us of any accommodations needed to ensure you have access to a fair and equitable process. Any information received relating to accommodation will be addressed confidentially .

