Job Details
Description
Reporting to the Regional Manager, Settlement & Structured Transactions, the Analyst will be responsible to collaborate in the management of settlement associated with energy market trading and structured transaction agreements.

Responsibilities

Ensure that daily and monthly settlement tasks are successfully completed;
Validate and fully understand the accounting entries done for invoices and month end estimates while respecting the accounting organizational standards;
Reconcile settlement statements and invoices;
Fully comprehend structured transaction agreements and corporate company structure;
Prepare invoices and month-end estimates for structured transaction agreements;
Fully comprehend market settlement and charge code algorithms to develop a shadow calculation and a validation process;
Fully comprehend charge code algorithms and the corporate structure in order to allocate the revenues and the charges to the right legal entities;
Conduct research and analysis to remain current with market rules that impact settlement and revenues;
Analyze current settlement processes, procedures and reports for continued optimization;
Ensure proper regulatory reporting to Regulatory Agencies and Governments;
Collaborate with various departments to ensure accuracy in financial and regulatory reports;
Track and meet obligations within structured transaction agreements to ensure compliance with contract terms;
Work with IT on systems improvements and upgrade projects;
Work with various departments and external counterparties to understand, document and resolve settlement disputes;
Support growth through due diligence, integration of new assets and new initiatives;
Support the Regional Manager, Settlement & Structured Transactions and provide various updates on daily activities.

Requirements

Enthusiastic learner with demonstrated ability to thrive in a fast paced work environment;
Strong analytical skills with excellent attention to detail; working in a conscientious, consistent and thorough manner;
Capable of achieving high quality results, increasing efficiency and productivity, to meet the organization’s standards;
Ability to locate and collect data from appropriate sources and analyze it to prepare meaningful and concise reports that summarize the information;
Remain energized and focused in the face of ambiguity, change or strenuous demands;
Strong organizational skills and the ability to work under tight deadlines;
Capable of solving problems and using sound judgment;
Excellent written and oral communications skills in English; French is an asset.

Qualifications

Undergraduate degree in Business Administration, Economics or a related financial/quantitative discipline;
Minimum two (2) years of relevant work experience in a related field, preferably energy;
Advanced Excel skills (i.e. Macros, Pivot Tables, PowerQuery);
Knowledge of reconciliation and validation software such as Open Access Technology International, Inc.(OATI) is an asset;
Knowledge of Industrial and Financial Systems (IFS) is an asset;
Knowledge of Trade capture and Data Validation Systems is an asset.

Company Description
Creating the unknown since 1997. At Ubisoft Montreal, we’re united by a common goal: to enrich players’ lives with original and memorable gaming experiences. We develop iconic franchises that engage millions around the world, like Assassin’s Creed, Far Cry, For Honor, Rainbow Six, Watch Dogs – and, well, we can’t disclose all our secrets just yet.
Our biggest strength is – and always will be – our people: the immensely talented team members surrounding, supporting, and producing the high-quality games that have made our studio what it is today.
When you join Ubi MTL, you’ll discover a workplace that sparks inspiration and connection: an environment with a variety of voices, identities, backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. We offer a collaborative space that provides career advancement, a host of learning opportunities, and meaningful benefits centred on well-being.

Here, our shared desire to dream big, take risks, and constantly improve contributes to the innovation and boundary-pushing that ultimately leads to our collective success.

Job Description
Ubisoft’s Office of the CIO (OCIO) is looking for an IT Portfolio Manager to work within the Strategic Planning team. The OCIO supports the entire IT organization by enabling teams to transform the CIO’s vision into reality.
Reporting to the IT Associate Director for Portfolio Management, you will act as a senior advisor to IT leadership on governance and best practices in Project Portfolio Management (PPM).The team is the hub for practices & tools to link strategy with execution, enable smart decisions on technology investments, and align IT value delivery to business needs. The team also enables IT governance by framing the master data used to run our business.
To succeed in this role, you will need demonstrable experience in IT governance, a desire to champion change and a lot of ambition. You will not receive clear mandates, but rather a vision and objectives. You will need strong analytical skills, an aptitude for solving complex problems, and a keen eye for detail. Great communication skills will be required to understand the needs of your peers and lead the organization towards maturity.
Responsibilities
Evolve our portfolio planning expertise by
Building new portfolio delivery methods & practices and guiding our partners in adopting them;
Providing clarity to IT leadership and business sponsors on proposed and ongoing investments;
Coordinating our portfolio planning activities, including prioritisation, funding & approval;
Establish IT Roadmapping practices by
Building relationships with your partners in IT and coaching portfolio leaders to increase their Portfolio Project Management (PPM) maturity;
Planning and creating the governance processes and maintaining the roadmap from ten IT departments;
Simplify, automate and repeat until the exercise becomes painless;
Guide IT governance towards simplicity by
Helping shape our IT master data architecture to be both simple & effective;
Consolidating our approach to service catalog management & project portfolio management;
Disseminating information clearly with effective communications and training.This position may require occasional travel overseas when COVID isn’t a thing anymore

Qualifications

You have experience in project, program or portfolio management, service management, finance or functional architecture;
You have knowledge of and/or have worked with PPM systems such as Planview, Planisware or others and collaboration tools such as Sharepoint, Confluence or Jira;
Experience in resource management is appreciated;
You have a solid knowledge of PMP, SAFE LPM or other methodologies;
You have a good understanding of financial planning and budgeting.
Additional Information
Just a heads up: If you require a work permit, your eligibility may depend on your education and years of relevant work experience, as required by the government.
Skills and competencies show up in different forms and can be based on different experiences, that's why we strongly encourage you to apply even though you may not have all the requirements listed above.
At Ubisoft, you can come as you are. We embrace diversity in all its forms. We’re committed to fostering a work environment that is inclusive and respectful of all differences.

With an annual budget of over $1B the Ottawa Hospital is a large complex organization, one of the largest of its kind in Canada.
The Financial Analyst – Capital is responsible for tracking capital expenditures and funding transactions, including calculating budgets and actual expenditures by project, tracking against forecast, monitoring the use of deferred capital contributions, and preparing related billings associated with the Capital Budget and Reporting processes at the Ottawa Hospital. This position will be responsible for the monthly updating and analysis of the construction-in-progress accounts, project budget variance reports and the fixed-asset sub-system.
The Financial Analyst – Capital will prepare month-end and year-end analysis of capital, construction-in-progress and deferred capital contribution balances as well as other requests and ensure that all necessary reporting to senior management and other stakeholders is submitted on a timely and accurate basis, to ensure proper use of funds and reporting of capital assets.

Rotation/Shifts


Days, 8 hour shifts.

Basic Requirements


Undergraduate Degree or College Diplomas in Commerce/or Accounting;
 CPA (CA/CMA/CGA) or working towards completion;
Three (3) to Five (5) years’ experience in financial analysis, preferably in a large, complex environment;
 Proficient with spreadsheets and reporting tools;
 Excellent interpersonal skills demonstrated through collaborative & productive relationships with various stakeholders and partners;
 Results oriented with the ability to prioritize multiple tasks and effectively manage time to successfully meet strict deadlines;
 Excellent communication skills both oral and written.

Preferred Qualifications


Experience with a large ERP financial systems (ORACLE);
 Knowledge of CIHI-MIS guidelines;
 Proficiency in English and French - oral expression (advanced level) and comprehension (advanced level).

