Develop and monitor KPIs, identify gaps between actual and expected results and create actionable recommendations to achieve targets;
Identify and implement process improvement initiatives and establish best practices;
Take the lead on projects and initiatives and prepare business cases for presentation;
Create financial models to evaluate business decisions and find opportunities within the organization;
Monthly and year-end G/L reconciliations, creating and posting journal entries;
Ensure controls are in place to safeguard the company’s assets;
Lead financial analysis coordinator(s) in month-end closing processes and preparing financial scorecards;
All other tasks/projects as assigned including ad-hoc reporting as assigned by the Senior Manager and Director of Finance.
What do you need to succeed?
Must-have
3 years of work experience in an analyst role;
University Degree is required;
Completion or enrolment in CPA;
Strong proficiency in MS Excel and PowerPoint;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to build relationships;
High level of accuracy and attention to detail;
Strong organizational skills, with the ability to multi-task and meet conflicting deadlines in a fast paced work environment;
Ability to work with minimal supervision and take initiative to make decisions.
Nice-to-have
Experience in a management role;
Experience with SAP;
Knowledge of VBA, SQL, SAS or other coding languages;
Bilingualism (English and French) is an asset.
