Job Description:
Reporting to the Director of Business Development, the Finance Manager is primarily responsible for the effective and efficient financial operations of Business Development. The incumbent is responsible for the development of multi-year budgets, providing analysis for strategic decision making and reporting to the College Budget Committee. The incumbent provides leadership and support related to the business operations of Business Development in several areas, including: financial and operational performance reporting, forecasting, revenue projections, allocation and procurement management, business model analysis, and vendor contract negotiations/recommendations.
Working closely with the Director and Department Managers, the incumbent plans, develops, organizes, directs and controls the annual budget process for the department. S/he prepares and organizes materials for budget deliberations, sets budget targets, and creates and composes narrative details to describe budget changes. S/he develops solutions and alternatives for balancing budgets or funding new initiatives and prepares both departmental annual and quarterly budget submissions and facilitates resolutions of variances. S/he assists the Director in the preparation of budgets for reporting to the Associate Vice President GOACL, Senior Vice President Academic and the College Budget Committee. The incumbent develops a budget tracking process and oversees the monthly budget performance of the department and provides planning, directions and strategic input with colleagues during quarterly reviews in Budget Preparation.
Within the scope and mandate of Business Development, the incumbent also supports and facilitates a variety of business development requirements including, but not limited to, contract negotiation, lead generation, memorandums of understanding/agreements, contract administration (terms and conditions, cost recovery, risk mitigation etc.) and other related duties as required.
The incumbent is familiar with the College Strategic and Business plans, the Business Development Strategic Plan/Business Plan, and overall College initiatives. S/he is able to communicate and work effectively with personnel at all levels both internally and externally.
Required Qualifications:
Minimum of a four (4) year degree in Business with major in Accounting or related field;
Certified Professional Accounting Designation (CPA) is required;
Minimum of nine (9) years of related experience in developing and managing complex budgets with large organization Financial Accounting/Budget/Human Resources and Student Information Systems.;
Solid experience in Advanced Excel and other MS Suite programs (Word, PowerPoint, Outlook), as well as Workday, Adaptive Insights, Power BI, Tableau and other reporting systems for report creation;
Ability to understand and apply General Business principles and Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP)
Strong capability in financial analysis and ability to communicate financial concepts and models, including their impact on academic operations;
Ability to understand and apply complex accounting principles and internal control standards in large organizations;
Ability to apply conflict resolution techniques in a business setting;
Strong leadership, supervisory and management skills;
Strong analytical and coordination skills;
Strong Project Management Skills;
Excellent planning, organizational and time management skills in order to evaluate, determine and implement or assign the correct course of action in a timely and effective matter;
Knowledge of lean process improvement approaches;
Ability to interpret/apply business policies procedures and systems;
Must understand client-centred customer service skills and be able to apply them;
Ability to interpret/apply business policies, procedures and systems;
Excellent interpersonal and communication (both verbal and written) skills.
