Overview

Our client operates in over 30 countries and manages over $600 billion of real assets focused on real estate, infrastructure, renewable power, private equity, and credit. Publicly traded company.

Is one of the world’s largest owners, operators, and developers of renewable power, with $59 billion of power assets under management. Our portfolio of hydropower, wind, utility-scale solar, distributed generation, and storage assets extends across North America, South America, Europe, India, and China, totaling over 21,000 megawatts of capacity, and nearly 6,000 generating facilities globally. Leveraging over 120 years of operating experience and industry-leading innovation, we drive value across our extensive clean energy platform and deliver innovative renewable power solutions that accelerate the world towards a low-carbon future. Our value extends well beyond the clean energy we produce to fuel a sustainable, growing economy. From our extensive renewable power fleet, we make positive economic, social, and environmental impacts in the communities where we live and work.

Our client attracts and retains high-performing individuals who are interested in making an impact and being part of a fast-paced and collaborative environment. Join our team to contribute to the success of one of the fastest growing and largest publicly traded, pure play renewable power platforms in the world while supporting decarbonization and greater energy sustainability to facilitate the global transition to a net-zero economy.

Reporting to the Senior Director, Financial Applications, the Senior Project Manager, Financial Applications will play a key role in planning, coordinating, and executing initiatives related to our Financial Applications.

Responsibilities

Direct, plan, organize and oversee all aspects and activities related to one or more projects at one time;
Supervise, guide, coach, and direct work of multiple direct reports, including technical and functional resources assigned to projects;
Develop, maintain, and monitor progress of project plans and budgets to ensure they are proceeding per timelines and targets;
Drive delivery of activities being performed and obtain input from project team members to provide regular reports on status to management;
Ensure adherence to Brookfield project management methodology while proactively recommend/identify areas for improvement in that methodology;
Proactively communicate and collaborate with decision-makers, system owners, and end-users to analyze information needs and requirements;
Maintain project data and repository of artifacts from stakeholders, project team, dependent programs to ensure complete and accurate project artifacts.
Requirements

Capable of working in a fast-paced environment; able to work effectively in ambiguous or changing situations; ability to manage time effectively;
Ability to coordinate multiple tasks, manage expectations and meet tight deadlines;
Self-starter, able to work independently without significant coaching or oversight;
Strong leadership skills and the ability to provide direction and coaching to team members;
Ability to identify problems and deal with situations and issues proactively;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to interact professionally and effectively with executives, managers, and subject matter experts;
Strong attention to detail with the ability to work in a conscientious, consistent, and thorough manner;
Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite, specifically Excel
Experience in the areas of application integration and methodologies, business process design, process re-engineering and continuous improvement;
Practical experience with internal control procedures and audit requirements in relation to data access, security and master data configuration would be an asset;
Experience with ERP systems (IFS, D365) and/or financial consolidation applications (Cognos Controller, One Stream).
﻿Qualifications

Minimum of 5 years of professional experience in an IT project delivery/management role
Bachelor’s degree in Business, Accounting, Information Technology or related field
English is essential; Ability to communicate in French is an asset
